# TERMS OF SERVICE                                                                                                                              
   
  **Last Updated: February 5, 2026**                                                                                                              
                                                                           
  ## 1. Acceptance of Terms

  By downloading, installing, or using Between (the "App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to
  these Terms, do not use the App. We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Your continued use of the App constitutes acceptance of
   such modifications.

  ## 2. Description of Service

  Between is a private communication and organization tool designed for shared use between two partners. The App allows users to send letters,
  store photographs on a shared map, and synchronize calendar events.

  ## 3. User Accounts and Security

  - **Account Creation:** You must register an account to access features. You agree to provide accurate information.
  - **Security:** You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials. You are fully responsible for all activities
  that occur under your account.
  - **Eligibility:** You must be at least 17 years of age to use this App.

  ## 4. User-Generated Content (UGC)

  The App allows you to post, upload, and share content, including photos, text, memory pins, and calendar entries ("User Content").

  - **Ownership:** You retain ownership of any content you upload. By uploading content, you grant Between a worldwide, non-exclusive,
  royalty-free license to use, store, and display that content solely for the purpose of providing the App's services to you and your connected
  partner.
  - **Prohibited Content:** You agree not to upload content that is illegal, abusive, harassing, threatening, pornographic, or otherwise
  objectionable.
  - **Content Moderation:** We have the right (though not the obligation) to review and remove any User Content that violates these Terms or
  Apple's App Store Review Guidelines.
  - **Reporting:** Users may report content they believe violates these Terms. We will review reports and take appropriate action, which may
  include removing content and suspending accounts.

  ## 5. Privacy and Data Permissions

  Your use of the App is also governed by our [Privacy Policy](privacy-policy.md).

  - **Device Permissions:** The App requires access to your device's camera, photo library, and location to function. By granting these
  permissions, you authorize the App to access and display this data within the shared interface.
  - **Private Nature:** We respect the private nature of the content shared in this App. We do not sell your personal data, notes, or photos to
  third parties.
  - **Law Enforcement:** We may disclose user data when required by law or in response to valid legal requests from law enforcement authorities.

  ## 6. Subscriptions and Purchases

  - **Between+:** The App offers an optional premium subscription ("Between+") that unlocks additional features including customization options,
  premium map styles, and increased limits.
  - **Billing:** Subscriptions are billed through Apple's App Store. Payment will be charged to your Apple ID account at confirmation of purchase.
  - **Renewal:** Subscriptions automatically renew unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.
  - **Cancellation:** You may manage and cancel subscriptions in your Apple ID account settings.

  ## 7. Apple-Specific Terms (Required for iOS)

  - **Acknowledgement:** These Terms are between you and Between, not Apple. Apple is not responsible for the App or its content.
  - **Maintenance:** Apple has no obligation to furnish any maintenance or support services for the App.
  - **Warranty:** In the event of any failure of the App to conform to any applicable warranty, you may notify Apple, and Apple will refund the
  purchase price (if any). To the maximum extent permitted by law, Apple will have no other warranty obligation.
  - **Third-Party Beneficiary:** Apple and Apple's subsidiaries are third-party beneficiaries of these Terms. Upon your acceptance, Apple will
  have the right to enforce these Terms against you.

  ## 8. Termination

  We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the App at our sole discretion, without notice, for conduct that we believe violates
   these Terms or is harmful to other users, us, or third parties, or for any other reason.

  ## 9. Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability

  The App is provided on an "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" basis. Between disclaims all warranties, express or implied. We are not liable for any
